      ],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "solution": "<p>Relation with HBr to give phenol</p>\n<p>(1) <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7mtlo4p/379c68d1-a280-447f-ad8e-4910bcb8ed5c/ecea6590-f4bf-11ef-8314-7569c5991ccb/file-jaoe38c1m7mtlo4q.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7mtlo4p/379c68d1-a280-447f-ad8e-4910bcb8ed5c/ecea6590-f4bf-11ef-8314-7569c5991ccb/file-jaoe38c1m7mtlo4q.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 21 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>The reaction involves two steps,</p>\n<p>$\\star$) The lone pair of oxygen atom attacks on the hydrogen of HBr.</p>\n<p>$\\star$) The nucleophile Br$^-$ attacks on the methyl group which lead to the formation of phenol along with methyl bromide.</p>\n<p>Phenol is formed from this compound on reaction with HBr.</p>\n<p>(2) <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7mtu8gp/6997a226-0d40-4f33-9a85-1b47ad78628f/db188490-f4c0-11ef-8314-7569c5991ccb/file-jaoe38c1m7mtu8gq.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7mtu8gp/6997a226-0d40-4f33-9a85-1b47ad78628f/db188490-f4c0-11ef-8314-7569c5991ccb/file-jaoe38c1m7mtu8gq.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 21 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>No phenol formation in this case because alkyl chain is attached to the benzene ring and on addition of H-Br, either H$^+$ or Br$^-$ get attached to this chain and no $-$OH group is formed as it is directly bonded to the benzene ring.</p>\n<p>(3) <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7mtwov9/05e920f0-e994-4ea7-aaa8-5dce58d5246d/1f62d150-f4c1-11ef-8314-7569c5991ccb/file-jaoe38c1m7mtwova.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7mtwov9/05e920f0-e994-4ea7-aaa8-5dce58d5246d/1f62d150-f4c1-11ef-8314-7569c5991ccb/file-jaoe38c1m7mtwova.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 21 English Explanation 3\"></p>\n<p>No phenol formation in this case. $-$OH group is formed as</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7mtzru9/ade18fd1-a5dd-4d03-9169-a8e6eec88142/751c0210-f4c1-11ef-8314-7569c5991ccb/file-jaoe38c1m7mtzrua.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7mtzru9/ade18fd1-a5dd-4d03-9169-a8e6eec88142/751c0210-f4c1-11ef-8314-7569c5991ccb/file-jaoe38c1m7mtzrua.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 21 English Explanation 4\"></p>\n<p>So, phenol product is formed in case of option (1) compound only.</p>",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers"
